Nothing seems wrong EXCEPT if you look at the kopernicus log file you can see it finds my planet with the configuration loader, but later it doesn't. Kopernicus does work, as KSS works. The .cfg is in GameData/CustomPlanets/KopernicusFiles.

Your much needed 5 year late reply.

First of all, your planet is VERY dense. That’s the least of your priorities, so add a vertex height map and colour map like they do in this post:

  

VertexHeightMap
				{
					map = (Filepath)/YourPlanet_height.dds
					offset = -500
					deformity = 3000.0
					scaleDeformityByRadius = false
					order = 20
					enabled = true
				}
				VertexColorMap
				{
					map = (filepath)/MyPlanet_color.dds
					order = 20
					enabled = true
				}

Do not copy these directly, there are some stuff to fill in. Refer to the page, under “step 8”.

Lastly, increase your scaled version fade start and fade end to a few thousand.
